The paper deals with a problem related to interval graphs, which are a well-studied class of graphs in computer science. The problem is a generalization of the recognition problem, which is a classic problem in graph theory and computational geometry. The algorithm proposed in the paper is based on PQ-trees, which is a data structure commonly used in computational geometry and graph algorithms. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), cs.CG (Computational Geometry), and cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics).
